he root jacocoTestReport is a harness wrapper that invokes the per-project task across matching coordinates.\\n\\n### Native-image modes\\n\\nLocal runs default to `current-defaults`.\\n\\nDuring the transition period, metadata CI runs both:\\n- `current-defaults`\\n- `future-defaults-all`\\n\\nSelect the future lane locally with `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all`.\\n\\n### Library stats\\n\\n`generateLibraryStats` writes exploded local stats files:\\n- `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json`\\n- One file per metadata-version directory\\n- Each local file contains the `versions` array for that metadata-version only\\n\\nSchema:\\n- `stats/schemas/library-stats-schema-v1.0.2.json`\\n\\n```console\\n./gradlew generateLibraryStats -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|group:artifact|k/n|all]\\n./gradlew validateLibraryStats\\n```\\n\\n- `generateLibraryStats`: recomputes selected coordinates and updates matching exploded stats files under `stats/`.\\n- `validateLibraryStats`: validates mirrored committed stats files, schema compliance, and normalized sorting without recomputing metrics.\\n\\nFor new-library issue triage, the repository also exposes:\\n\\n```console\\n./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version\\n```\\n\\nThis resolves the requested library, runs Native Image with `Preserve` and `TrackDynamicAccess`, and prints a JSON summary suitable for issue comments.\\n\\n### Generating Metadata\\n\\nGenerates metadata for a single library coordinate. If `agentAllowedPackages` is provided, a new user-code-filter.json will be created or updated from those packages or from package roots derived from the resolved library JAR.\\n\\n- `coordinates`: group:artifact:version (single coordinate only)\\n- `agentAllowedPackages`: comma-separated package list, `fromJar`, or `-` for none\\n\\nExamples:\\n   ```console\\n   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3\\n   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\\n   ./gradlew generateMetadata -Pcoordinates=org.postgresql:postgresql:42.7.3 --agentAllowedPackages=org.example.app,com.acme.service\\n\\n[93 more lines in file. Use offset=201 to continue.]\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777292263589}]}\n315:[tool-call] delta {\"command\":\"find . -path '*kotlin-stdlib-common*' -o -path '*jetbrains*' | head -100 && rg \\\"kotlin-stdlib-common|stdlib-common\\\" -n .\",\"timeout\":10}\n316:[tool-call] end id=call_TH5gYMEPLi0pzidQdUqQWpYF|fc_0d7cd990c572df5d0169ef53e8e930819db550ea0247a4b02f name=bash args={\"command\": \"find . -path '*kotlin-stdlib-common*' -o -path '*jetbrains*' | head -100 && rg \\\"kotlin-stdlib-common|stdlib-common\\\" -n .\", \"timeout\": 10}\n317:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0d7cd990c572df5d0169ef53e884ac819d94c2faa331433151\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp71PosNm76kqOiDxDJ5Sg9x2bnrX8x-KR9YRVT6ljikZzP58acya5CUR-cGrBn6Yjjp0qFVUJ2z81L4Oh63a-KqWs6Pp3ek9qOoGurEfQdM8J6JpBIJ-jY7V2Jaj4244ELtbM755qyOcDP1-eVIs55CAaG0Ir6pZ6DpNEeYisE0PlD9ulx2zUinYD-52QiFHmpP0OjlYnGlRoNtbyzUp4CxgXoAAoQY3fUcLRwSUs08BiZBEzaWxhJdRu1mUuZ9oqwcDaiQnyWmSVwx7tlAsDux5NjBuCzU7oyMpD-tPKmFYa7xBBV375ppapN6rja2Avq_kg2m-q6yudWmQnqvJfwOiOtVUpFcbAHUPVBM_qyV6iyBmXvaVJj1vnX46WrrlVEe2f_Bkc20ErhgRV6HAKXjm4cE2dkO_Ux9LdZtd0FKWzU82ePwUK5-smWjpV2z5ex0myb8byN-64r4kxZr7BZROGxtPknCwUjiTAdzbvUZEZQXIKX-sIKRFP2P_T8cRLWohJUQPQU8M8s_D4gISUUqCiO8sJZPYeX1lNH-FARcgFFzBCx1hcbPdikRwU3RGt7q1KW57AKrNC4NnVJE2F2gAYdA-RtOOvBy0WqJygq6VICxBkm-d3L9F_PbJIIScyxSDe-TsoxgBmh-UJJEx_qfehpaNj7IWaoZnX_SFzvl1-lqt41fgUu_PGYapH4knl-hLPfVlL67UpkV8M3YDRfFvMpunwVr5_qq7K1BUJiFc0O2s6xm6hzsvd9kPm6MC-ShOQwieVQ4DlYt0o-XADj9WMa9gYlU_2-SN8xp1XwkPpjdFgIz2b52F9GtUKeGaQXykMSKTtsmiWEaBcEhWjvN-oCOqVxiZbJXEeyKCx8NmL