groupBy` handles mapping, `groupingBy` is about lazy grouping operations. I need to be careful to prevent overlap, ensuring my Result functions are consistent. I can test some scenarios involving exceptions, like handling `NumberFormatException`. This could help clarify how these features work and how well the error handling functions in practice.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Refining parsing logic**\\\\n\\\\nI'm simplifying my error handling with the `runCatching` features. The first part parses a positive number and maps it for a success message. If the parse fails, it captures the error message. For the recovery process, I'm handling `IllegalArgumentException` by replacing it with a value of 1 for negatives. Lastly, I'm checking for division by zero, which should raise an `ArithmeticException`. It’s important to ensure that the `parsePositive` function adheres to its preconditions!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_19HSEMRN5VrMZ3ICdUJ5EG3z|fc_0d7cd990c572df5d0169ef54092c4c819dba119b37032dfd1c\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-stdlib-common/1.3.72/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_stdlib_common/Kotlin_stdlib_commonTest.kt\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    @Test\\n    fun preconditionsThrowTheDocumentedExceptionTypes() {\\n        assertThatThrownBy { require(false) { \\\"invalid argument\\\" } }\\n            .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException::class.java)\\n            .hasMessage(\\\"invalid argument\\\")\\n\\n        assertThatThrownBy { check(false) { \\\"invalid state\\\" } }\\n            .isInstanceOf(IllegalStateException::class.java)\\n            .hasMessage(\\\"invalid state\\\")\\n\\n        assertThat(\\\"metadata\\\".takeIf { it.startsWith(\\\"meta\\\") }).isEqualTo(\\\"metadata\\\")\\n        assertThat(\\\"metadata\\\".takeUnless { it.length > 20 }).isEqualTo(\\\"metadata\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun coroutinePrimitivesResumeContinuationsAndCombineContexts() {\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    fun preconditionsThrowTheDocumentedExceptionTypes() {\\n        assertThatThrownBy { require(false) { \\\"invalid argument\\\" } }\\n            .isInstanceOf(IllegalArgumentException::class.java)\\n            .hasMessage(\\\"invalid argument\\\")\\n\\n        assertThatThrownBy { check(false) { \\\"invalid state\\\" } }\\n            .isInstanceOf(IllegalStateException::class.java)\\n            .hasMessage(\\\"invalid state\\\")\\n\\n        assertThat(\\\"metadata\\\".takeIf { it.startsWith(\\\"meta\\\") }).isEqualTo(\\\"metadata\\\")\\n        assertThat(\\\"metadata\\\".takeUnless { it.length > 20 }).isEqualTo(\\\"metadata\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun resultsComposeSuccessFailureAndRecoveryPaths() {\\n        val quotas = mapOf(\\\"images\\\" to 4, \\\"documents\\\" to 8)\\n\\n        val scaled = runCatching { readQuota(quotas, \\\"documents\\\") }\\n            .map { quota -> quota * 3 }\\n            .fold(\\n                onSuccess = { quota -> \\\"allowed:$quota\\\" },\\n                onFailure = { error -> \\\"missing:${error.message}\\\" },\\n            )\\n        assertThat(scaled).isEqualTo(\\\"allowed:24\\\")\\n\\n        val fallback = runCatching { readQuota(quotas, \\\"audio\\\") }\\n            .recover { error ->\\n                assertThat(error).isInstanceOf(NoSuchElementException::class.java)\\n                1\\n            }\\n        assertThat(fallback.isSuccess).isTrue()\\n        assertThat(fallback.getOrThrow()).isEqualTo(1)\\n\\n        val failedComputation = runCatching { readQuota(quotas, \\\"images\\\") }\\n            .mapCatching { quota -> quota / (quota - 4) }\\n        assertThat(failedComputation.isFailure).isTrue()\\n        assertThat(failedComputation.exceptionOrNull()).isInstanceOf(ArithmeticException::class.java)\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    fun coroutinePrimitivesResumeContinuationsAndCombineContexts() {\"}, {\"oldText\": \"    private suspend fun suspendEcho(value: String): String = suspendCoroutine { continuation ->\\n        continuation.resume(\\\"echo:$value\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    private data class Transaction(val category: String, val amount: Int)\", \"newText\": \"    private suspend fun suspendEcho(value: String): String = suspendCoroutine { continuation ->\\n        continuation.resume(\\\"echo:$value\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    private fun readQuota(quotas: Map<String, Int>, name: String): Int =\\n        quotas[name] ?: throw NoSuchElementException(\\\"No quota named $name\\\")\\n\\n    private data class Transaction(val category: String, val amount: Int)\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 560, \"output\": 2076, \"cacheRead\": 12800, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 15436, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777292281287, \"responseId\": \"resp_0d7cd990c572df5d0169ef53f99ad4819d8b64b4974157f343\"}}\n1089:[tool-exec] end id=call_19HSEMRN5VrMZ3ICdUJ5EG3z|fc_0d7cd990c572df5d0169ef54092c4c819dba119b37032dfd1c name=edit status=success\n1093:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Testing grouping and exceptions**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether grouping is fully covered. It seems like `groupBy` is separate from `groupingBy`, and that each has its unique uses. While `groupBy` handles mapping, `groupingBy` is about lazy grouping operations. I need to be careful to prevent overlap, ensuring my Result functions are consistent. I can test some scenarios involving exceptions, like handling `NumberFormatException`. This could help clarify how these features work and how well the error handling functions in practice.\\n\\n**Refining parsing logic**\\n\\nI'm simplifying my error handling with the `runCatching` features. The first part parses a 